subSubSection.paragraph:
ABDOMEN. Tergites sparsely tomentose. A thin, pale median line along the whole length of the insect may or may not be present. The colour of the tergites is mostly chequered light/dark red-brown or brown (
Fig. 8E
). Nymphs may be uniform brown.
